Story 8 — Parse and Validate LLM Output
As a developer
I want to parse and validate the LLM output inside the Lambda
So that every entity value is checked by code before being accepted
What needs to happen:

Strip markdown fences from LLM output if present
Parse the JSON string into a Go struct
Verify expected entity keys exist in the parsed output
If parsing fails → set all entities to NILL and add to missing list
Loop through each entity individually:
Confidence check:

Below threshold → REJECT → NILL

For CONSTRAINED entities:

Value in allowed list → ACCEPT
Not in list → REJECT → NILL

For OPEN entities:

Passes format validation → ACCEPT
Fails validation → REJECT → NILL


LLM output is never trusted directly — code makes all decisions

Done when:

Parsing works correctly for clean and messy LLM output
All validation rules enforced by code
Fallback works correctly when parsing fails
Unit tests written for every validation rule
Unit tests written for fallback path
All unit tests pass

